<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Solving over-constrained situation for block-level non-replaced elements in normal flow</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visudet.html#the-width-property" />
        <meta name="flags" content="interact" />
        <meta name="assert" content="When direction is 'ltr', margin-right is ignored in an over-constrained situation." />
        <style type="text/css">
            body
            {
                margin: 0;
                padding-right: 100px;
                direction: ltr;
            }
            #d1
            {
                display: block;
                width: 100px; /* Forcing the container to be less than the width of its contents. */
                background: green;
                float: right;
                height: 20px;
            }
            #d2
            {
                float: right;
                background-color: green;
                width: 50px;
                height: 20px;
            }
            p
            {
                position: absolute;
                top: 80px;
                left: 10px;
            }
            span
            {
                display: block;
                width: 200px;
                margin-left: 10px;
                margin-right: 10px;
                padding-left: 10px;
                padding-right: 10px;
                background-color: green;
                border-left: solid green 10px;
                border-right: solid green 10px;
                height: 20px;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <div id="d1">
            <span></span>
        </div>
        <div id="d2"></div>
        <p>Test passes if no white space is between the green box and the right edge of the page.</p>
    </body>
</html>